    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 17,
        "summary": "He who is glad at calamities will be punished\u2014A friend loves at all times\u2014Even a fool, when he holds his peace, is counted wise.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Better is a dry morsel, and quietness therewith, than an house full of sacrifices with strife.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:17.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise servant shall have rule over a son that causeth shame, and shall have part of the inheritance among the brethren.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The fining pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold: but the Lord trieth the hearts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mal. 3:3 (2\u20133); D&C 128:24.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 17:10.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wicked doer giveth heed to false lips; and a liar giveth ear to a naughty tongue.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso mocketh the poor reproacheth his Maker: and he that is glad at calamities shall not be unpunished.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:31; Mosiah 4:17 (16\u201318). TG\u00a0Mocking.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Poor.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 31:29 (28\u201329); Prov. 24:17; Obad. 1:12.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 829
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Children's children are the crown of old men; and the glory of children are their fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Family, Patriarchal.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Duties of; Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Excellent speech becometh not a fool: much less do lying lips a prince.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A gift is as a precious stone in the eyes of him that hath it: whithersoever it turneth, it prospereth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that covereth a transgression seeketh love; but he that repeateth a matter separateth very friends.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0forgives a transgression.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0promotes a loving relationship.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 64:9 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A reproof entereth more into a wise man than an hundred stripes into a fool.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reproof.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "An evil man seeketh only rebellion: therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let a bear robbed of her whelps meet a man, rather than a fool in his folly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 13:8.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso rewardeth evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Evil.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The beginning of strife is as when one letteth out water: therefore leave off contention, before it be meddled with.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:8.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 136:23 (23\u201334).",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that justifieth the wicked, and he that condemneth the just, even they both are abomination to the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Injustice.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:24; Isa. 5:23.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore is there a price in the hand of a fool to get wisdom, seeing he hath no heart to it?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A friend loveth at all times, and a brother is born for adversity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man void of understanding striketh hands, and becometh surety in the presence of his friend.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He loveth transgression that loveth strife: and he that exalteth his gate seeketh destruction.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:23.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hath a froward heart findeth no good: and he that hath a perverse tongue falleth into mischief.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 101:4.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that begetteth a fool doeth it to his sorrow: and the father of a fool hath no joy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:1; 17:25.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A merry heart doeth good like a medicine: but a broken spirit drieth the bones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cheerful.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:13; D&C 59:15 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wicked man taketh a gift out of the bosom to pervert the ways of judgment.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bribe.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wisdom is before him that hath understanding; but the eyes of a fool are in the ends of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:6.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 2:14.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A foolish son is a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bare him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:21.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Also to punish the just is not good, nor to strike princes for equity.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hath knowledge spareth his words: and a man of understanding is of an excellent spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:19; James 1:19.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0is cool of spirit (i.e., reserved).",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Even a fool, when he holdeth his peace, is counted wise: and he that shutteth his lips is esteemed a man of understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 13:5.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:11; Amos 5:13.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}